    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/109b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MIN1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-03T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>430. After consultation with <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1"
                        >McCormick</persName> it has been decided negotiations of agreement with
                    Sweden should be carried on in London. <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> returning from Paris
                    this week to take up this question with British and French and will try to reach
                    some understanding.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
